        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>__doc_gr_radar_find_max_peak_c</name>
        <initializer>= R&quot;doc(This block estimates a single peak of a given FFT spectrum as tagged stream. Output is a message with the information of frequency, phase and power of the peak as a f32vector with a single item. All data is tagged with the identifiers (symbols) &apos;frequency&apos;, &apos;phase&apos; and &apos;power&apos;. The peak is estimated on the whole spectrum or on the range max_freq if cut_max_freq is true. Furthermore a threshold of the spectrum amplitude can be given with threshold. The DC peak can be cut out with the protected samples samp_protect. This value do not evaluate samp_protect samples around the DC peak. If no suitable peak is found the block returns empty vectors with the identifiers.

Constructor Specific Documentation:

